Local hard caps for image payloads + grim/grimblast support in
the screenshot tool.

Why
---

omniroute is fronted by Angie with `client_max_body_size 1m`
(verified by curl probe: <=1_048_464 B passes through; >=1_064_848 B
returns 413). gptme as shipped:

  - `view_image` only resizes when the *file* is bigger than 1 MB,
    but the wire payload is base64-encoded JSON wrapping the image
    — a 910 KB PNG explodes to ~1.21 MiB on the wire and trips the
    gateway. We tighten the trigger to 384 KiB so the base64 image
    content stays comfortably under ~512 KiB, leaving room for the
    system prompt and chat history inside the 1 MiB envelope. The
    resize loop now keeps shrinking (bounded to 5 attempts, 256 px
    floor) so we cannot accidentally emit something too big.

  - `screenshot.py` only knows `gnome-screenshot` (Wayland) and
    `scrot` (X11). Under Hyprland we have `grim` (and optionally
    `grimblast`); without one of these in the dispatch table the
    tool raises `NotImplementedError`. We add both, preferring
    grimblast (handles geometry/clipboard niceties) then grim,
    keeping gnome-screenshot as a last Wayland fallback.

Drop both hunks once gptme upstream addresses them.

